Troubleshooting Tips
Issue: Frida cannot connect to device

Verify ADB connection: adb devices
Restart ADB server: adb kill-server && adb start-server
Check USB debugging is enabled on device/emulator
Issue: Script fails to hook methods

Verify correct class and method names using jadx or similar decompiler
Ensure application is running before attaching
Check for obfuscation that may change class names
Issue: Python scripts fail with import errors

Install Frida Python bindings: pip3 install frida-tools
Verify Python version compatibility (3.8+)
Check virtual environment activation if applicable
Conclusion
This lab provided hands-on experience with Frida's CLI toolkit for dynamic mobile application security testing. Students learned to intercept and modify application behavior at runtime, identify common vulnerabilities, and automate testing workflows using Python. These skills are essential for mobile application penetration testing and security research. Continue practicing by analyzing additional vulnerable applications and expanding your automation frameworks to cover more attack vectors.
